__NAME__ purpose
specify error log filename
__END__


__NAME__ synopsis
<arg choice='plain'><replaceable>filename</replaceable></arg>
__END__


__NAME__ description
Specify the error log file location. 
</para><para>
The Interchange daemon must have the permission to create and write to the
specified file.
</para><para>
When using the directive on a &glos-catalog; level, specifying absolute
filenames might not be allowed due to &conf-NoAbsolute;.
__END__

__NAME__ see also
SysLog
__END__


__NAME__ example: Setting ErrorFile
<programlisting>
ErrorLog /var/log/interchange/error.log
</programlisting>
__END__

